2a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2001-02-24T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SST", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2001/sst33hb1262a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 16607, "bill_version_id": 88794, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2001-01-29T10:24:29-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to establish procedures to resolve certain disagreements regarding overhead or underground facilities crossing railroad rights-of-way. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 49-16A-100 be amended to read as follows: 49-16A-100. The public utilities commission shall make promulgate rules and regulations pursuant to chapter 1-26 for the setting of poles on railroad right-of-way, and the stringing or suspending of telephone, telegraph, electric, or other wires over the track of railroads. If public convenience and necessity require that overhead or underground facilities of common carriers, public utilities, rural water systems, or municipalities cross over or under railroad right-of-way located outside of public grounds, streets, alleys, and highways in this state, and the owners of the facilities and the railroad right-of-way have failed to agree upon the terms and conditions or compensation for the same, the commission, after notice and hearing, may prescribe reasonable terms, conditions, and compensation under which the crossing shall be permitted. No compensation may be required of any common carrier for crossing railroad right-of-way within public grounds, streets, alleys, and highways in this state. 450 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.021 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 16607, "bill_version_id": 89912, "bill_version": "House State Affairs Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2001-02-13T11:40:20-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow for reasonable attorney's fees in stockholder litigation. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 47-7-34 be amended to read as follows: 47-7-34. The circuit court shall have full power to liquidate the assets and business of a corporation and grant or deny reasonable attorney's fees, whether or not the corporation is liquidated, in an action by a shareholder when it is established: (1) That the directors are deadlocked in the management of the corporate affairs and the shareholders are unable to break the deadlock, and that irreparable injury to the corporation is being suffered or is threatened by reason thereof; or (2) That the acts of the directors or those in control of the corporation are illegal, oppressive , or fraudulent; or (3) That the shareholders are deadlocked in voting power, and have failed, for a period which included at least two consecutive annual meeting dates, to elect successors to directors whose terms have expired or would have expired upon the election of their successors; or (4) That the corporate assets are being misapplied or wasted."}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 16607, "action_date": "2001-01-29T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 88862, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/88862.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 246, "committee_id_action": 712, "committee_id_assigned": 707, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 16607, "action_date": "2001-02-12T19:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 89866, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/89866.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 707, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 16607, "action_date": "2001-02-12T19:00:00-06:00", "document_id